<h1>Debari Park - Dinosaur Theme Park</h1>
<p>We promised the kids that we would take them to a dino-theme park. They were screaming about this place for 5 days, and finally, we made it. It's not Jurassic Park, but it does have plenty of things to do. There are a few dinosaur exhibits, then a small zoo, where you can see a couple turtles, feed some meerkats and guinea pigs (if you purchase a cup of carrots). The Northern black tegu, which looks 1/2 iguana and 1/2 komodo dragon, was my favorite animal. Then the kids go upstairs, where they can do some physical activities like going down a giant slide, bowling. Then it's outside to the dino-theme park, which includes a climbing wall, putt-putt, playland, and plenty more. There are actually 2 theme parks, and next to Debari Park is <a href="http://cocomongjeju.com/main.html" target="_blank">Cocomong Eco Park</a>.</p>
